<subSubSection pageId="1" pageNumber="396" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="1.[151,1437,574,1931]" pageId="1" pageNumber="396">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,266,574,599]" pageId="1" pageNumber="396">Diagnosis</emphasis>
. The strongly bilobate condition of the labrum (
<figureCitation box="[822,903,574,599]" captionStart="FIGURES 1 – 13" captionStartId="2.[151,264,1825,1847]" captionTargetBox="[162,1436,198,1789]" captionTargetId="figure@2.[162,1447,193,1790]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURES 1 – 13. Menieroclerus nigropiceus: (1) hind wing (‘ a’ showing basal limit of CuA 1 + 2); (2 – 3) male tegmen (ps = phallobasic strut, pa = phallobasic apodeme), (2) dorsal, (3) lateral; (4) male phallus; (5) male spicular fork; (6) male pygidium; (7) female pygidium; (8) male sixth ventrite; (9) female sixth ventrite; (10) metendosternite; (11) male head with arrows indicating each side of bifurcated labrum; (12) male pronotal and elytral base (lateral view) — (12 a) arrow indicating location of baso-lateral pronotal pit, (12 b) arrow pointing to laterally binodulate elytral puncture; (13) securiform terminal maxillary palpomere [scale bars = 1 mm (Fig. 1), 0.5 mm (Figs. 2 – 12), 0.25 mm (Fig. 13)]." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/257194/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="396">Fig. 11</figureCitation>
) is possibly unique among 
<taxonomicName box="[1222,1320,574,599]" class="Insecta" family="Cleridae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="396" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="family">Cleridae</taxonomicName>
; however, even if it is not unique then the following characters in combination are diagnostic for 
<taxonomicName box="[1173,1335,610,635]" class="Insecta" family="Cleridae" genus="Menieroclerus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="396" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus" status="gen. n.">
<emphasis box="[1173,1335,610,635]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="396">Menieroclerus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis bold="true" box="[1346,1429,610,635]" pageId="1" pageNumber="396">
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[1346,1429,610,635]" pageId="1" pageNumber="396" rank="genus">gen. n.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
: terminal maxillary palpomeres securiform (
<figureCitation box="[657,745,646,671]" captionStart="FIGURES 1 – 13" captionStartId="2.[151,264,1825,1847]" captionTargetBox="[162,1436,198,1789]" captionTargetId="figure@2.[162,1447,193,1790]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURES 1 – 13. Menieroclerus nigropiceus: (1) hind wing (‘ a’ showing basal limit of CuA 1 + 2); (2 – 3) male tegmen (ps = phallobasic strut, pa = phallobasic apodeme), (2) dorsal, (3) lateral; (4) male phallus; (5) male spicular fork; (6) male pygidium; (7) female pygidium; (8) male sixth ventrite; (9) female sixth ventrite; (10) metendosternite; (11) male head with arrows indicating each side of bifurcated labrum; (12) male pronotal and elytral base (lateral view) — (12 a) arrow indicating location of baso-lateral pronotal pit, (12 b) arrow pointing to laterally binodulate elytral puncture; (13) securiform terminal maxillary palpomere [scale bars = 1 mm (Fig. 1), 0.5 mm (Figs. 2 – 12), 0.25 mm (Fig. 13)]." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/257194/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="396">Fig. 13</figureCitation>
); gular sutures very weakly divergent (appearing parallel); elytron with ten rows of deep, laterally nodulate punctures (
<figureCitation box="[849,935,682,707]" captionStart="FIGURES 1 – 13" captionStartId="2.[151,264,1825,1847]" captionTargetBox="[162,1436,198,1789]" captionTargetId="figure@2.[162,1447,193,1790]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURES 1 – 13. Menieroclerus nigropiceus: (1) hind wing (‘ a’ showing basal limit of CuA 1 + 2); (2 – 3) male tegmen (ps = phallobasic strut, pa = phallobasic apodeme), (2) dorsal, (3) lateral; (4) male phallus; (5) male spicular fork; (6) male pygidium; (7) female pygidium; (8) male sixth ventrite; (9) female sixth ventrite; (10) metendosternite; (11) male head with arrows indicating each side of bifurcated labrum; (12) male pronotal and elytral base (lateral view) — (12 a) arrow indicating location of baso-lateral pronotal pit, (12 b) arrow pointing to laterally binodulate elytral puncture; (13) securiform terminal maxillary palpomere [scale bars = 1 mm (Fig. 1), 0.5 mm (Figs. 2 – 12), 0.25 mm (Fig. 13)]." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/257194/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="396">Fig. 12</figureCitation>
b); tibiae longitudinally carinate; tibial spur formula 2–2–2; tarsal pad formula 4–4–4 (basitarsal pads substantially smaller than those of tarsomeres 2–4), tarsal pads not divided into paired lobes (
<figureCitation box="[545,628,754,779]" captionStart="FIGURES 14 – 16" captionStartId="3.[151,264,1165,1187]" captionTargetBox="[153,1436,193,1137]" captionTargetId="figure@3.[151,1436,193,1144]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURES 14 – 16. Menieroclerus nigropiceus: (14) female specimen (scale = 1 mm); (15) female mesotarsus showing nonbifid tarsal pads (scale = 0.5 mm); (16) distribution." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/257195/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="396">Fig. 15</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="1.[151,1437,574,1931]" pageId="1" pageNumber="396">
<taxonomicName box="[199,362,790,815]" class="Insecta" family="Cleridae" genus="Menieroclerus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="396" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus" status="gen. n.">
<emphasis box="[199,362,790,815]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="396">Menieroclerus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis bold="true" box="[370,452,790,815]" pageId="1" pageNumber="396">
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[370,452,790,815]" pageId="1" pageNumber="396" rank="genus">gen. n.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
differs from 
<taxonomicName box="[605,767,790,815]" class="Insecta" family="Cleridae" genus="Thanasimodes" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="396" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[605,767,790,815]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="396">Thanasimodes</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(= ‘T’) in the following character states: Labrum bilobate (emarginate in ‘T’); gular sutures parallel (convergent in ‘T’); procoxal cavities posteriorly broadly open (narrowly open to completely closed in ‘T’); tarsal pads not incised (incised in ‘T’); two protibial spurs (none in ‘T’); pretarsal claws appendiculate (simple in ‘T’); elytral punctation nodulate (without nodules in ‘T’); base of CuA1+2 of hindwing detached from CuA (attached to CuA in ‘T’); tegminal phallobasic struts not fused to apodeme (fused to apodeme in ‘T’).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection lastPageId="3" lastPageNumber="398" pageId="1" pageNumber="396" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="1.[151,1437,574,1931]" pageId="1" pageNumber="396">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,337,1006,1031]" pageId="1" pageNumber="396">Description</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis box="[354,422,1006,1031]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="396">Head.</emphasis>
Eyes large, coarsely facetted, frontal rim strongly margined, emarginate above antennal socket; antennae with 11 antennomeres, flagellomeres increasingly dilated towards 
<collectingRegion box="[1111,1133,1043,1067]" country="Nigeria" name="Rivers" pageId="1" pageNumber="396">A</collectingRegion>
9, 
<collectingRegion box="[1162,1183,1043,1067]" country="Nigeria" name="Rivers" pageId="1" pageNumber="396">A</collectingRegion>
9–10 cupuliform, 
<collectingRegion box="[1389,1411,1043,1067]" country="Nigeria" name="Rivers" pageId="1" pageNumber="396">A</collectingRegion>
11 subovate; terminal labial palpomere securiform, maxillary palpomere securiform (
<figureCitation box="[1131,1221,1078,1103]" captionStart="FIGURES 1 – 13" captionStartId="2.[151,264,1825,1847]" captionTargetBox="[162,1436,198,1789]" captionTargetId="figure@2.[162,1447,193,1790]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURES 1 – 13. Menieroclerus nigropiceus: (1) hind wing (‘ a’ showing basal limit of CuA 1 + 2); (2 – 3) male tegmen (ps = phallobasic strut, pa = phallobasic apodeme), (2) dorsal, (3) lateral; (4) male phallus; (5) male spicular fork; (6) male pygidium; (7) female pygidium; (8) male sixth ventrite; (9) female sixth ventrite; (10) metendosternite; (11) male head with arrows indicating each side of bifurcated labrum; (12) male pronotal and elytral base (lateral view) — (12 a) arrow indicating location of baso-lateral pronotal pit, (12 b) arrow pointing to laterally binodulate elytral puncture; (13) securiform terminal maxillary palpomere [scale bars = 1 mm (Fig. 1), 0.5 mm (Figs. 2 – 12), 0.25 mm (Fig. 13)]." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/257194/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="396">Fig. 13</figureCitation>
); labrum strongly bilobate, lobes extending over mandibles (
<figureCitation box="[632,715,1114,1139]" captionStart="FIGURES 1 – 13" captionStartId="2.[151,264,1825,1847]" captionTargetBox="[162,1436,198,1789]" captionTargetId="figure@2.[162,1447,193,1790]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURES 1 – 13. Menieroclerus nigropiceus: (1) hind wing (‘ a’ showing basal limit of CuA 1 + 2); (2 – 3) male tegmen (ps = phallobasic strut, pa = phallobasic apodeme), (2) dorsal, (3) lateral; (4) male phallus; (5) male spicular fork; (6) male pygidium; (7) female pygidium; (8) male sixth ventrite; (9) female sixth ventrite; (10) metendosternite; (11) male head with arrows indicating each side of bifurcated labrum; (12) male pronotal and elytral base (lateral view) — (12 a) arrow indicating location of baso-lateral pronotal pit, (12 b) arrow pointing to laterally binodulate elytral puncture; (13) securiform terminal maxillary palpomere [scale bars = 1 mm (Fig. 1), 0.5 mm (Figs. 2 – 12), 0.25 mm (Fig. 13)]." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/257194/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="396">Fig. 11</figureCitation>
); gular sutures very weakly divergent (appearing parallel), post gular process a short, slender, bifurcated central sclerite with paired, weakly defined, setose lobes. 
<emphasis box="[1247,1336,1150,1175]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="396">Thorax.</emphasis>
Pronotal disc without median sulcus, subapical depression reasonably well-defined; postero-lateral pits present (
<figureCitation box="[1324,1408,1186,1211]" captionStart="FIGURES 1 – 13" captionStartId="2.[151,264,1825,1847]" captionTargetBox="[162,1436,198,1789]" captionTargetId="figure@2.[162,1447,193,1790]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURES 1 – 13. Menieroclerus nigropiceus: (1) hind wing (‘ a’ showing basal limit of CuA 1 + 2); (2 – 3) male tegmen (ps = phallobasic strut, pa = phallobasic apodeme), (2) dorsal, (3) lateral; (4) male phallus; (5) male spicular fork; (6) male pygidium; (7) female pygidium; (8) male sixth ventrite; (9) female sixth ventrite; (10) metendosternite; (11) male head with arrows indicating each side of bifurcated labrum; (12) male pronotal and elytral base (lateral view) — (12 a) arrow indicating location of baso-lateral pronotal pit, (12 b) arrow pointing to laterally binodulate elytral puncture; (13) securiform terminal maxillary palpomere [scale bars = 1 mm (Fig. 1), 0.5 mm (Figs. 2 – 12), 0.25 mm (Fig. 13)]." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/257194/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="396">Fig. 12</figureCitation>
a); procoxal cavities broadly open, prosternal process with small terminal expansion; mesoventrite with rounded anterior process; elytron elongate, disc with ten rows of deep punctures, punctures laterally nodulate (
<figureCitation box="[1323,1407,1258,1283]" captionStart="FIGURES 1 – 13" captionStartId="2.[151,264,1825,1847]" captionTargetBox="[162,1436,198,1789]" captionTargetId="figure@2.[162,1447,193,1790]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURES 1 – 13. Menieroclerus nigropiceus: (1) hind wing (‘ a’ showing basal limit of CuA 1 + 2); (2 – 3) male tegmen (ps = phallobasic strut, pa = phallobasic apodeme), (2) dorsal, (3) lateral; (4) male phallus; (5) male spicular fork; (6) male pygidium; (7) female pygidium; (8) male sixth ventrite; (9) female sixth ventrite; (10) metendosternite; (11) male head with arrows indicating each side of bifurcated labrum; (12) male pronotal and elytral base (lateral view) — (12 a) arrow indicating location of baso-lateral pronotal pit, (12 b) arrow pointing to laterally binodulate elytral puncture; (13) securiform terminal maxillary palpomere [scale bars = 1 mm (Fig. 1), 0.5 mm (Figs. 2 – 12), 0.25 mm (Fig. 13)]." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/257194/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="396">Fig. 12</figureCitation>
b), discal vestiture composed of paired sensilla (i.e., each long seta with minute accompanying sensillum at its base), each stria with a single setal pair on the upper anterior rim of each puncture, each interstria with single row of setal pairs; metathoracic wing with CuA1+2 vein narrowly separated from CuA (may appear connected due to continuation of pigmentation to CuA; see 
<figureCitation box="[627,692,1402,1427]" captionStart="FIGURES 1 – 13" captionStartId="2.[151,264,1825,1847]" captionTargetBox="[162,1436,198,1789]" captionTargetId="figure@2.[162,1447,193,1790]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURES 1 – 13. Menieroclerus nigropiceus: (1) hind wing (‘ a’ showing basal limit of CuA 1 + 2); (2 – 3) male tegmen (ps = phallobasic strut, pa = phallobasic apodeme), (2) dorsal, (3) lateral; (4) male phallus; (5) male spicular fork; (6) male pygidium; (7) female pygidium; (8) male sixth ventrite; (9) female sixth ventrite; (10) metendosternite; (11) male head with arrows indicating each side of bifurcated labrum; (12) male pronotal and elytral base (lateral view) — (12 a) arrow indicating location of baso-lateral pronotal pit, (12 b) arrow pointing to laterally binodulate elytral puncture; (13) securiform terminal maxillary palpomere [scale bars = 1 mm (Fig. 1), 0.5 mm (Figs. 2 – 12), 0.25 mm (Fig. 13)]." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/257194/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="396">Fig. 1</figureCitation>
); metendosternite as in 
<figureCitation box="[965,1077,1402,1427]" captionStart="FIGURES 1 – 13" captionStartId="2.[151,264,1825,1847]" captionTargetBox="[162,1436,198,1789]" captionTargetId="figure@2.[162,1447,193,1790]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURES 1 – 13. Menieroclerus nigropiceus: (1) hind wing (‘ a’ showing basal limit of CuA 1 + 2); (2 – 3) male tegmen (ps = phallobasic strut, pa = phallobasic apodeme), (2) dorsal, (3) lateral; (4) male phallus; (5) male spicular fork; (6) male pygidium; (7) female pygidium; (8) male sixth ventrite; (9) female sixth ventrite; (10) metendosternite; (11) male head with arrows indicating each side of bifurcated labrum; (12) male pronotal and elytral base (lateral view) — (12 a) arrow indicating location of baso-lateral pronotal pit, (12 b) arrow pointing to laterally binodulate elytral puncture; (13) securiform terminal maxillary palpomere [scale bars = 1 mm (Fig. 1), 0.5 mm (Figs. 2 – 12), 0.25 mm (Fig. 13)]." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/257194/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="396">Figure 10</figureCitation>
. 
<emphasis box="[1088,1149,1404,1427]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="396">Legs.</emphasis>
Lateral surfaces of tibiae longitudinally carinate; tibial spur formula 2–2–2; tarsomere formula 5–5–5; all basitarsi reduced in length (no visible dorsal surface); tarsal pad formula 4–4–4, basitarsal pads extremely small, pads of T2–4 conspicuous, increasing is size towards T4, pads not divided into paired lobes (i.e., apical margins not divided or emarginate) (
<figureCitation box="[159,246,1546,1571]" captionStart="FIGURES 14 – 16" captionStartId="3.[151,264,1165,1187]" captionTargetBox="[153,1436,193,1137]" captionTargetId="figure@3.[151,1436,193,1144]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURES 14 – 16. Menieroclerus nigropiceus: (14) female specimen (scale = 1 mm); (15) female mesotarsus showing nonbifid tarsal pads (scale = 0.5 mm); (16) distribution." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/257195/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="396">Fig. 15</figureCitation>
); each side of pretarsal claw with a triangular basal denticle. 
<emphasis box="[974,1088,1546,1571]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="396">Abdomen.</emphasis>
Six ventrites. 
<emphasis box="[1261,1436,1546,1571]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="396">Male genitalia.</emphasis>
Tegmen with phallobasic struts not fused to apodeme (
<figureCitation box="[790,904,1582,1607]" captionStart="FIGURES 1 – 13" captionStartId="2.[151,264,1825,1847]" captionTargetBox="[162,1436,198,1789]" captionTargetId="figure@2.[162,1447,193,1790]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURES 1 – 13. Menieroclerus nigropiceus: (1) hind wing (‘ a’ showing basal limit of CuA 1 + 2); (2 – 3) male tegmen (ps = phallobasic strut, pa = phallobasic apodeme), (2) dorsal, (3) lateral; (4) male phallus; (5) male spicular fork; (6) male pygidium; (7) female pygidium; (8) male sixth ventrite; (9) female sixth ventrite; (10) metendosternite; (11) male head with arrows indicating each side of bifurcated labrum; (12) male pronotal and elytral base (lateral view) — (12 a) arrow indicating location of baso-lateral pronotal pit, (12 b) arrow pointing to laterally binodulate elytral puncture; (13) securiform terminal maxillary palpomere [scale bars = 1 mm (Fig. 1), 0.5 mm (Figs. 2 – 12), 0.25 mm (Fig. 13)]." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/257194/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="396">Figs. 2, 3</figureCitation>
); phallus relatively simple with slender distal process (
<figureCitation box="[250,319,1618,1643]" captionStart="FIGURES 1 – 13" captionStartId="2.[151,264,1825,1847]" captionTargetBox="[162,1436,198,1789]" captionTargetId="figure@2.[162,1447,193,1790]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURES 1 – 13. Menieroclerus nigropiceus: (1) hind wing (‘ a’ showing basal limit of CuA 1 + 2); (2 – 3) male tegmen (ps = phallobasic strut, pa = phallobasic apodeme), (2) dorsal, (3) lateral; (4) male phallus; (5) male spicular fork; (6) male pygidium; (7) female pygidium; (8) male sixth ventrite; (9) female sixth ventrite; (10) metendosternite; (11) male head with arrows indicating each side of bifurcated labrum; (12) male pronotal and elytral base (lateral view) — (12 a) arrow indicating location of baso-lateral pronotal pit, (12 b) arrow pointing to laterally binodulate elytral puncture; (13) securiform terminal maxillary palpomere [scale bars = 1 mm (Fig. 1), 0.5 mm (Figs. 2 – 12), 0.25 mm (Fig. 13)]." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/257194/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="396">Fig. 4</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="1.[151,1437,574,1931]" box="[199,426,1654,1679]" pageId="1" pageNumber="396">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,288,1654,1679]" pageId="1" pageNumber="396">Gender</emphasis>
. Masculine.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="1.[151,1437,574,1931]" lastBlockId="3.[151,1436,1262,1756]" lastPageId="3" lastPageNumber="398" pageId="1" pageNumber="396">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,459,1690,1715]" pageId="1" pageNumber="396">Systematic placement</emphasis>
. By process of elimination, 
<taxonomicName box="[780,1081,1690,1715]" class="Insecta" family="Cleridae" genus="Menieroclerus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="396" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="nigropiceus" status="comb. n.">
<emphasis box="[780,1081,1690,1715]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="396">Menieroclerus nigropiceus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis bold="true" box="[1090,1193,1690,1715]" pageId="1" pageNumber="396">
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[1090,1193,1690,1715]" pageId="1" pageNumber="396">comb. n.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
is negatively defined as a member of the subfamily 
<taxonomicName box="[491,586,1726,1751]" class="Insecta" family="Cleridae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="396" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subFamily" subFamily="Clerinae">Clerinae</taxonomicName>
simply due to the absence of the following morphological attributes: fourth tarsosomeres minute and hidden between lobes of third tarsomeres (= 
<taxonomicName box="[968,1106,1762,1787]" class="Insecta" family="Cleridae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="396" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subFamily" subFamily="Korynetinae">Korynetinae</taxonomicName>
<emphasis box="[1116,1232,1762,1787]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="396">sensu lato</emphasis>
); first tarsomeres well developed, dorsally visible between second tarsomere and tibial distal margin and pretarsal claw tripartite (= 
<taxonomicName box="[151,242,1834,1859]" class="Insecta" family="Cleridae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="396" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subFamily" subFamily="Tillinae">Tillinae</taxonomicName>
); apodeme of male tegmen long and membranously connected to phallobase (= Epiclininae); labrum large, generally not emarginate and eyes with ocular notch absent or minutely developed (= 
<taxonomicName box="[1109,1272,1870,1895]" class="Insecta" family="Cleridae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="396" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subFamily" subFamily="Hydnocerinae">Hydnocerinae</taxonomicName>
). No formallyestablished genus-groupings (i.e., tribes) have been proposed for 
<taxonomicName box="[916,1014,1906,1931]" class="Insecta" family="Cleridae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="396" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subFamily" subFamily="Clerinae">Clerinae</taxonomicName>
. Several informal clerine sub-groups, however, have been preliminarily proposed: the 
<taxonomicName box="[704,779,1262,1287]" class="Insecta" family="Cleridae" genus="Clerus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="398" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[704,779,1262,1287]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="398">Clerus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
-series (containing 
<taxonomicName box="[998,1133,1262,1287]" class="Insecta" family="Cleridae" genus="Thanasimus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="398" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[998,1133,1262,1287]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="398">Thanasimus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName box="[1149,1275,1263,1286]" class="Insecta" family="Cleridae" genus="Stigmatium" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="398" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[1149,1275,1263,1286]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="398">Stigmatium</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName box="[1335,1436,1262,1287]" class="Insecta" family="Cleridae" genus="Omadius" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="398" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[1335,1436,1262,1287]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="398">Omadius</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
genus-groups), and the 
<taxonomicName box="[430,526,1299,1324]" class="Insecta" family="Cleridae" genus="Orthrius" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="398" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[430,526,1299,1324]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="398">Orthrius</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
-group (
<bibRefCitation author="Gerstmeier" box="[621,819,1299,1324]" pageId="3" pageNumber="398" refString="Gerstmeier, R. (2002) Generic concept of clerid taxa related to Clerus (Coleoptera: Cleridae: Clerinae). Entomological Problems, 32 (2), 99 - 111." type="journal article" year="2002">Gerstmeier 2002</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation author="Gerstmeier" box="[836,1153,1299,1324]" pageId="3" pageNumber="398" refString="Gerstmeier, R. &amp; Eberle, J. (2011) Definition and revision of the Orthrius - group of genera (Coleoptera, Cleridae, Clerinae). ZooKeys, 92, 35 - 60. http: // dx. doi. org / 10.3897 / zookeys. 92.1157" type="journal article" year="2011">Gerstmeier &amp; Eberle 2011</bibRefCitation>
), though the securiform terminal maxillary palpomeres of 
<taxonomicName box="[532,700,1336,1359]" class="Insecta" family="Cleridae" genus="Menieroclerus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="398" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="nigropiceus" status="comb. n.">
<emphasis box="[532,700,1336,1359]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="398">M. nigropiceus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis bold="true" box="[707,810,1334,1359]" pageId="3" pageNumber="398">
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[707,810,1334,1359]" pageId="3" pageNumber="398">comb. n.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
prevent its inclusion in any of them.
</paragraph>
<caption httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/257194/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="397" targetBox="[162,1436,198,1789]" targetPageId="2">
<paragraph blockId="2.[151,1436,1825,2001]" pageId="2" pageNumber="397">
