<paragraph blockId="3.[151,1436,1262,1756]" pageId="3" pageNumber="398">
The taxon-diverse subfamily 
<taxonomicName box="[541,636,1371,1396]" class="Insecta" family="Cleridae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="398" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subFamily" subFamily="Clerinae">Clerinae</taxonomicName>
is yet to be adequately defined morphologically or established as a monophylum (
<bibRefCitation author="Kolibac" box="[315,472,1406,1431]" pageId="3" pageNumber="398" refString="Kolibac, J. (1997) Classification of the subfamilies of Cleridae (Coleoptera: Cleroidea). Acta Musei Moraviae, Scientiae Naturales, 81, 307 - 361." type="journal article" year="1997">Kolibáč 1997</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation author="Opitz" box="[483,614,1406,1431]" pageId="3" pageNumber="398" refString="Opitz, W. (2010) Classification, natural history, phylogeny, and subfamily composition of the Cleridae and generic content of the subfamilies (Coleoptera: Cleroidea). Entomologica Basiliensia et Collectionis Frey, 32, 31 - 128." type="journal article" year="2010">Opitz 2010</bibRefCitation>
). 
<collectingRegion box="[632,652,1407,1431]" country="Nigeria" name="Rivers" pageId="3" pageNumber="398">A</collectingRegion>
preliminary molecular phylogeny-estimate of 
<taxonomicName box="[1175,1270,1406,1431]" class="Insecta" family="Cleridae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="398" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="family">Cleridae</taxonomicName>
suggested that the exclusion of 
<taxonomicName box="[341,498,1443,1468]" class="Insecta" family="Cleridae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="398" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subFamily" subFamily="Hydnocerinae">Hydnocerinae</taxonomicName>
from 
<taxonomicName box="[569,664,1443,1468]" class="Insecta" family="Cleridae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="398" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subFamily" subFamily="Clerinae">Clerinae</taxonomicName>
renders the latter paraphyletic (
<bibRefCitation author="Gunter" box="[1026,1241,1443,1468]" pageId="3" pageNumber="398" refString="Gunter, N. L., Leavengood, J. M., Bartlett, J. S., Chapman, E. G. &amp; Cameron, S. L. (2013) A molecular phylogeny of the checkered beetles and a description of Epiclininae a new subfamily (Coleoptera: Cleroidea: Cleridae). Systematic Entomology, 38 (3), 626 - 636. http: // dx. doi. org / 10.1111 / syen. 12019" type="journal article" year="2013">
Gunter 
<emphasis box="[1114,1172,1443,1468]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="398">et al.</emphasis>
2013
</bibRefCitation>
). 
<collectingRegion box="[1261,1281,1443,1467]" country="Nigeria" name="Rivers" pageId="3" pageNumber="398">A</collectingRegion>
morphologybased character analysis of clerine and hydnocerine (plus anthicoclerine) genera could be a first step in understanding if/how the genera of 
<taxonomicName box="[547,642,1515,1540]" class="Insecta" family="Cleridae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="398" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subFamily" subFamily="Clerinae">Clerinae</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName box="[695,852,1515,1540]" class="Insecta" family="Cleridae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="398" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subFamily" subFamily="Hydnocerinae">Hydnocerinae</taxonomicName>
are related. The threefold usefulness of such a study would be to: a) test the monophyly of 
<taxonomicName box="[590,685,1550,1575]" class="Insecta" family="Cleridae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="398" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subFamily" subFamily="Clerinae">Clerinae</taxonomicName>
in relation to the inclusion/exclusion of 
<taxonomicName box="[1149,1310,1550,1575]" class="Insecta" family="Cleridae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="398" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subFamily" subFamily="Hydnocerinae">Hydnocerinae</taxonomicName>
; b) test the monophyly of previously proposed informal clerine groupings; and, c) potentially identify genus-groupings among genera not yet arranged into informal groupings. 
<collectingRegion box="[712,732,1623,1647]" country="Nigeria" name="Rivers" pageId="3" pageNumber="398">A</collectingRegion>
moderately large scale study such as this would be necessary before the systematic position of 
<taxonomicName box="[523,686,1659,1684]" class="Insecta" family="Cleridae" genus="Menieroclerus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="398" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus" status="gen. n.">
<emphasis box="[523,686,1659,1684]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="398">Menieroclerus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis bold="true" box="[692,772,1659,1684]" pageId="3" pageNumber="398">
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[692,772,1659,1684]" pageId="3" pageNumber="398" rank="genus">gen. n.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
within 
<taxonomicName box="[857,952,1659,1684]" class="Insecta" family="Cleridae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="398" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subFamily" subFamily="Clerinae">Clerinae</taxonomicName>
is understood.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="3.[151,1436,1262,1756]" pageId="3" pageNumber="398">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,442,1694,1719]" pageId="3" pageNumber="398">Known distribution</emphasis>
(
<figureCitation box="[463,553,1694,1719]" captionStart="FIGURES 14 – 16" captionStartId="3.[151,264,1165,1187]" captionTargetBox="[153,1436,193,1137]" captionTargetId="figure@3.[151,1436,193,1144]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURES 14 – 16. Menieroclerus nigropiceus: (14) female specimen (scale = 1 mm); (15) female mesotarsus showing nonbifid tarsal pads (scale = 0.5 mm); (16) distribution." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/257195/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="398">Fig. 16</figureCitation>
). Ethiopia, Kenya, Namibia, Republic of South Africa, Tanzania, Yemen, Zimbabwe.
</paragraph>
